"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly sets the x-axis ticks and labels. The `set_xticks` method expects a list of positions (floats or integers), not datetime objects. Additionally, `set_xticklabels` should be used with the same number of labels as ticks, and it should be called after `set_xticks`.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19c19,20\\n<ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n---\\n>ax.set_xticks(range(len(df.date.unique())))\\n>ax.set_xticklabels(labels=[d.strftime('%Y-%m-%d') for d in df.date.unique()], rotation=45)\"\n}"